</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Eric Horvitz</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:AI_expert_Eric_Horvitz_of_Microsoft.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/AI_expert_Eric_Horvitz_of_Microsoft.png/220px-AI_expert_Eric_Horvitz_of_Microsoft.png" width="220" height="300" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/AI_expert_Eric_Horvitz_of_Microsoft.png/330px-AI_expert_Eric_Horvitz_of_Microsoft.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/50/AI_expert_Eric_Horvitz_of_Microsoft.png 2x" data-file-width="440" data-file-height="600" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:AI_expert_Eric_Horvitz_of_Microsoft.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>
Eric Horvitz</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Eric Joel Horvitz</b> is an American computer scientist, and Technical Fellow at <a href="/wiki/Microsoft" title="Microsoft">Microsoft</a>, where he serves as managing director of <a href="/wiki/Microsoft_Research" title="Microsoft Research">Microsoft Research</a>'s main Redmond lab.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
<div id="toctitle">
